<br>
Each of these sets was done with a fresh, newly cast 63 fire pet. So it would be full mana, thus giving consistancy and to show potential as wizards rightly pointed out about casting a new pet each fight.<br>
<br>
However, because it is a FRESH pet each time, there is no time to buff it with *items*! No haste mask, proc weapons or belts for stats. Cannot have it both ways, wizards!<br>
<br>
it is buffed only with Burnout3 because that stacks with pets self buffs, doesnt over write arch shielding. Burnout5 gives better haste and +atk, but casting that once per pet, ie once per fight, would be a pain in ass unless you had the shield from saryn that casts BO5..and NOT MANY mages have that. Many mages though have velious legs with free BO3 buff, however. <br>
<br>
If wizards point out that reclaiming pets gives a net bonus of mana...no it DOESNT on the 63 pet because Reclaim Energy works based on the pets hit points, the fire pets have LESS hit points than other pets and DO NOT give +mana back because they have so few hit points, ergo, if you cast BO5 on them it would be a net mana loss per pet cast/buff.<br>
<br>
So each test lasted approx 60 seconds as best as I could do it, on banker in Katta for comparisons:<br>
<br>
Round1:<br>
Melee 1280hp<br>
Markars clash x2<br>
Draught of Fire x2<br>
Enticemement of Flame x2<br>
<br>
Assuming spells all hit for max, thats 56 DPs.<br>
<br>
Round 2 was almost identical to Round 1, won't bother posting it as its only about 100 hps difference.<br>
<br>
Round 3<br>
Melee 76 hp (yes 76 hp)<br>
Rend x1<br>
Ice Comet x2<br>
Enticement of Flame x1<br>
Draught of Fire x1<br>
Elnericks Entombment of Ice x1<br>
<br>
Assuming all spells hit for max thats 79 DPs. That was pretty good and about best you get.<br>
<br>
Those pets casting is extremely random, ocassionally chaining nukes, sometimes not, sometimes casting snare/roots a lot.<br>
<br>
Should get a comparative run with other pets to be 100%, but air 61 pet does 50-70 DPs, 62 water 70-90 DPs typically on high XP mobs.<br>
<br>
<br>
These pets run out of juice very quickly, their ability to cast spells lasts about 2--3 minutes of continous combat. Note that is NOT continous casting! <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.silverblades-suitcase.com"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.silverblades-suitcase.com/sb.gif"alt="Silverblades Suitcase"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=silverbladetheenchanter>Silverblade the Enchanter</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.silverblades-suitcase.com/artofadreamer/3d/excaliburthumb1.jpg" BORDER=0> at: 5/19/03 12:02:36 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=faramir42>Faramir42</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 40<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/19/03 12:16 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: *FACTS* on new mage pets</span><hr size=1> Guess what. I don't care what you parsed. I don't care about numbers.<br>
<br>
What is really going in here is most mages WANT this to go live. And many them don't care if it steps on wizards. There are many mages that want castable roots, snares, ice spells, concussion spells, you name it, they want it. <br>
<br>
Having pets isn't good enough for you. Having summoned items isn't good enough for you. Having awesome damage shields isn't good enough for you. You have debuff spells that give you a better chance to land spells. You've got shield spells. I'm always hearing mages wanting stuff they don't have, and what they do have to be better.<br>
<br>
Yeah, there are wizards that want more. But for the most part, we just want what we have to be better then it is now. Which is something mages have been complaining about to Sony for years. Make mages better.<br>
<br>
I bet if wizards asked for call of the hero, mages would cry NO! And why shouldn't we have it? It's more in line then with what wizards do then what mages do. We are masters of teleporting people around, mages are the master of summoing items. If we wanted our familars to act like pets, you would say NO! If we wanted damage shields like yours, You would say NO! Why shouldn't we have damage shields like yours? We are masters of damage, so good damage shields seem like a natural function of wizards.<br>
<br>
Yeah, there are wizards that want this. But like I said, what we mostly want is to have our current spells made better. Maybe you also don't realize is that often many of our spells have been made usless by Sony. Often the best we get for new spells is several older spells combined in one.<br>
<br>
Well I have no problems with improving a pet that isn't in line with other pets. But they don't have to just copy wizard spells, spells that have LONG been our specialty and hand it ove to a pet.<br>
<br>
Mages keep saying, Our fire pet sucks, this makes them better so shut up wizards. When us wizards are saying, Hey, sure you pet may suck and we don't have a problem with them being made stronger, but don't just hand them stuff a wizard is known for. <br>
<br>
