<br>
PS: if you want to know why wizards are acting bit furious about this idea, it's because how we are being treated the last time.<br>
<br>
Our epic bugged for months.<br>
Our spell lines given away to other classes. On raid, i can only outdamage on main boss. Every trash mob i cast mostly the exact damage as druids or magi's. Mob is beaten up fast, if i would use my fast nukes(which would allow me to nuke for more damage) i get aggro. So i either got to cast just 1 low/fast damage nuke or cast 1 big spell, but the big spell is hardly that much extra damage.<br>
<br>
Our ports and teleport spells are still EXPENSIVE for low lvl wizards, although their use is practically not interesting anymore. I really wonder how lower lvl wizzies can really buy them, unless they received donations to buy the spells.<br>
<br>
We don't get any upgrade for our main cold type nuke. Sure we have eci-flame, means we can upgrade our 2 lvl 60 nukes.(most people only got 1 of those)<br>
<br>
We still don't have any funny spells. There is more then just damage, people would love some funny spells, that have not really any use for xp.<br>
<br>
We got some lowbie DS, now if they would just extend the duration time on these, when we grow in level, but nope, their duration keeps so short, that it's not interesting to cast them.<br>
<br>
As wizard we also are handicapped, that we basically have 7 or 6 spellslots left. Not memming harvest is just not possible, because we just need the extra mana, to keep up with the other classes. Playing without a root memmed is also risky as wizard, since it's basically our only defence. They should just make some harvest another skill, instead of a spell.<br>
<br>
People expect us to punt for free, so they don't have to walk 1 zone.(yet we still have to buy these fragments 3 zones away, soe just don't want to place the fragments on pok shopkeepers)<br>
<br>
Basically every wizard stinks compared to other classes, unless they get some aa, then they start to be balanced again.<br>
<br>
Wizards barely can farm &quot;green mobs&quot; zones for tradeskill items. Unlike melee/pet people. Amount of mana per green mob is just too great.<br>
<br>
Wizards always have to hear, they are the master solo class, which is not really truth. They are just one of the better solo classes together with some others.<br>
<br>
The game environment is lately based on melee/healer/slower groups. Example: the amount of caster mobs is practically nihil in xp zones. And caster mobs are the opponents, where burst damage is good and required.<br>
<br>
Basically as wizard, we hope to stay an original class, instead of being downgraded to just some group &quot;nuke pet&quot;. More and more of our qualities are given to other classes and that's nto a good thing.<br>
<br>
(ok back to work now. Sorry no time, to read it over and fix some errors or erasing dumb arguments this time)<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
